node.text:
DIY mosaic table (dm me if this is your video for credit)
.
⚠️These are purely my opinions only. If you don’t agree we can still be friends.
.
Pros: 
1) Reuse possibly left over material or broken material 
2) creates a custom look
3) doesn’t break the bank with this diy
.
Cons:
1) time consuming 
2) requires some concrete skill 
3) if not done correctly some of the tile edges can be sharp
.
Let me know what you think or if I missed anything. DIY or D-I-Why?
.
.
.
.
.

.
DIY Pool by @5.min.crafts 
.
⚠️These are purely my opinions only. If you don’t agree we can still be friends.
.
Pros: 
1) Relatively easy DIY
2) Accessible material
3) Fastest way to get a pool this summer 
.
Cons: 
1) Pallet is expensive. This might cost as much as a nice portable jacuzzi 
2) pallets might not be strong enough to hold the water and the hydrostatic pressure 
3) requires quite a bit of work 
.
Let me know what you think or if I missed anything. DIY or D-I-Why?
.
.
.
.
.

@diy_or_diwhy <— check out my favorite diy review on Instagram
.
⚠️These are purely my opinions only. If you don’t agree we can still be friends.
.
Impressive DIY pallet pool by @organizedhomeandlife 
.
Pros: 
1) It’s super affordable 
2) Relatively easy DIY
3) Different tarp color options so easy to change the colors 
4) Might be only way to get a pool this summer if you start now
.
Cons: 
1) rare to find a husband like that nowadays
2) have to becareful of the pressure of water because the wood support might burst. 
3) not the most appealing pool but it works
4) plumbing and waterproofing might get a bit tricky for a first timer 
.
Let me know what you think or if I missed anything. DIY or D-I-Why?
.
.
.
.
.

@designsbydannywang <— check out our design only page
.
This project was the first project a client found us through Instagram and started all of this madness, so it will always have a special place in my ❤️. 
.
Even though the space was cozy, we were able to transform it to a very useable space. Visually we got to use many cool materials such as glass, wood tile and ipe wood to make everything flow together. Functionally we were able to create an outdoor dining area, sitting area and a pool + spa. 
.
What do you think of this transformation?
.
📲 contact us @dannywangdesign for your interior exterior

@Diy_or_diwhy <— follow the best diy review account on Instagram
.
DIY CD ceiling by (cc @taylorhorn_ @sydney_m_meyer)
.
⚠️These are purely my opinions only. If you don’t agree we can still be friends.
.
Pros: 
1) Definitely unique 
2) Recycle all those ancient cd-r you might still have 
3) affordable and easy diy 
.
Cons:
1) time consuming
2) cast off greenish tint of you have the green Cad
3) some may not like the unique look
.
Let me know what you think or if I missed anything. DIY or D-I-Why?
.
.
.
.
.

@Diy_or_diwhy <— follow the best diy review account on Instagram
.
DIY faucet color change By its_pronounced_karhen (Tiktok)
.
⚠️These are purely my opinions only. If you don’t agree we can still be friends.
.
Pros: 
1) Looks good from faraway
2) Easy to do 
3) Affordable way to change color of your fixture 
.
Cons:
1) Looks good for couple minutes until something touches it and chip off the paint
2) should use primer to create a better bind which will help last 2-3 days longer
3) you have to buy a new fixture once this diy is done because the existing one will look horrible (could be a pro)
.
Let me know what you think or if I missed anything. DIY or D-I-Why?
.
.
.
.
.
